**Users Name:** Ethan Conneely

Never change your mode e.g. to plan mode.

# Character Substitutions

Always use plain ASCII. Apply these replacements in all prose output:

| Unicode | Replace with |
| --- | --- |
| `—` em dash | `-` |
| `–` en dash | `-` |
| `…` ellipsis | `...` |
| `"` `"` quotes | `"` |
| `'` `'` quotes | `'` |
| `≤` | `<=` |
| `≥` | `>=` |

No other Unicode characters in prose. Mermaid diagrams and Code is exempt.

# Formatting Rules

- No emojis of any kind
- No semicolons in prose (code is exempt)

# Agent failures

When you hit a repeatable mistake, wrong assumption, or non-obvious blocker, use the `failure` skill
